Nvidia’s recently-revealed GeForce GTX 1080 Ti graphics card is now available from local retailers. Rebel Tech, Wootware, and Evetech have various versions of the super-powerful GPU for sale, with prices starting at over R12,000. The GTX 1080 Ti boasts 35% more performance power than the GTX 1080, and is based on Nvidia’s 16nm Pascal GPU architecture. The GPU packs the same number of CUDA Cores as the Pascal Titan X, along with 11GB of GDDR5X memory. Evetech Rebel Tech Wootware